Package frc.robot.subsystems

Contains all the base function code of each physical subsystem on the robot.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Climber
    Climber class that consists of two motors and a slightly complicated means of control.
    DriveTrain
    DriveTrain class that consists of four motors assembled in a tank drive configuration using the white 6" (dia.) wheels, with all set up done in order to have working odometry for accurate trajectory following.
    Indexer
    Indexer class that consists of a single motor that transports power cells from the Pickup to the Shooter.
    Limelight
    Limelight class that consists of a Limelight 2.0.
    Pickup
    Pickup class that consists of a single motor that either intakes or outtakes power cells.
    Pivot
    Pivot class that consists of a single motor that aids in extending the Pickup from the perimeter of the robot frame.
    Shooter
    Shooter class that consists for two motors and a janky velocity PID loop.
